news.title: China builders hit by downgrades as Evergrande deadline looms
news.para: Shares of Kaisa Group were hardest-hit, losing nearly a fifth of their value on Thursday after rating agency downgrades that highlighted the company's limited access to funding and significant U.S. dollar debt obligations.

news.title: Court dismisses bail plea of Ambience Group's promoter in money laundering case
news.para: The ED had raided Gehlot, his company Aman Hospitality Private Limited (AHPL), some other firms of the Ambience group, director in the company Dayanand Singh, Mohan Singh Gehlot, and their associates in July last year.

news.title: Salesforce leases seven lakh sq ft of office space in Hyderabad
news.para: "The lease has a lock-in period of 3 years and commands a rent of Rs 71 per sq ft. The deal was registered earlier this month," mentioned a document shared by Propstack.

news.title: China builders propose debt restructuring, maturity extension to regulators: Sources
news.para: The meeting underlines the behind-the-scenes efforts by China's debt-laden developers and regulators to contain the fallout centred around embattled China Evergrande Group.

news.title: SWAMIH fund exits from CCI Rivali Park's project in Mumbai
news.para: The project was launched in 2010 and got stalled due to lack of funds. Last mile funding helped in generating cash flows for existing lenders, delivering 700+ homes in Rivali Park and unlocking of capital for developers and investors.

news.title: ASK Property Investment Advisors to set up fund business in GIFT City
news.para: ​In addition, ASK Real Estate Fund -2, sponsored by ASK Property Investment Advisors (ASKPIA), has obtained clearance for a real estate focused fund of funds as category III Alternative Investment Fund (AIF), according to a statement issued by GIFT City on Thursday.

news.title: DNR Group & Hines to invest Rs 650 crore to develop project in Bengaluru
news.para: An initial investment of Rs 200 crore has already been made in the project. DNR Group and Hines entered into a partnership in 2020 to develop the project.

news.title: Eldeco raises Rs 275 crore debt from Tata Capital Housing Finance
news.para: The first project is a 2.1 million square feet project in Noida and the second one is a 1.2 million square feet project in Sohna, Gurugram.

news.title: Ahmedabad development body drafted 80 town planning schemes in past five years
news.para: ​​Recently Ahmedabad Urban Development Authority presented a report where it claimed that between 2016 and 2020 some 80 town planning maps were prepared covering an area of 11,441 hectares.

news.title: HC issues notice to Telangana government on new land law
news.para: PIL was filed by former deputy CM Damodar Raja Narasimha who questioned the new land law that brought in the new digital platform, Dharani portal, but forgot to borrow several key provisions from its parent Act, Record of Rights Act, 1971, which was repealed and replaced by the new land Act, 2020.

news.title: Construction cost up, builders say homes to get costlier
news.para: Independent sources in the home loan business say there has already been a 9-10% increase in prices of real estate in upper and upper middle class localities of the city. Another hike is expected if the rates do not stabilize soon.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Occupant's name to be removed from residential property tax bill
news.para: "Property tax amount remains unchanged regardless of whether the property is occupied by the owner or if has been given on rent,” said Jainik Vakil, chairman of AMC’s revenue committee.

news.title: The Executive Centre to invest Rs 200 crore for expansion in three cities
news.para: The flexible workspace industry has become more relevant for organisations amid the pandemic as companies across sectors reassess their real estate holdings, both long-term and short-term, to make capital expenditure more efficient.

news.title: Tax relief on bonds to offset property sale gain stands despite broker delay: ITAT
news.para: Income-tax liability that arises from long-term capital gains on sale of immovable property can be reduced by purchase of bonds eligible under section 54-EC. However, to avail of the exemption, it is vital that the investment is made within six months of the sale of the property.

news.title: Maharashtra nod to not revise capital value of buildings, land in Mumbai
news.para: Under the Mumbai Municipal Corporation Act, 1888, the capital value, based on which property tax is paid, is to be revised every five years.
